title.narrative: National capacities are strengthened to promote and support inclusive ECE and integrated ECI policies for the most vulnerable children.

description.narrative: The national Human Milk Bank that supports survival, care and nutrition of the most vulnerable infants across the country was established after years of advocacy and strong UNICEF support in partnership with the Ministry of Health and the Clinical Hospital Zagreb. Through a partnership with UNICEF Regional Office, the CO continued to strengthen the system and increase national capacities for delivering quality ECI services by using the newest technologies in support of young children with complex communication needs | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/08/2020

actual.value: 2020:Human Milk Bank is additionally equipped with delivery vehicle for milk collection and distribution. Other activities are on track with challenges due to the pandemic outbreak.

title.narrative: Availability of methodology with recommendations for implementation of MFHI standards in to all Maternity hospitals

baseline.value: There is no developed methodology for implementation of MFHI standards in to Maternity hospitals

actual.value: 2020:Implementation manual is finalized and is in the process of peer review. Activities are ongoing but take more time due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

title.narrative: Level of knowledge or skills of trained professionals on how to apply developmentally appropriate practices in ECI programmes and services to foster optimal learning and development in children aged 0-8 years

baseline.value: To be assessed at the beginning of programme

actual.value: 2020: In June and July, 380 Professional attended the first part of online training on AAC. The second part will take place in September.

title.narrative: Availability of fully functional open-source AAC app and Croatian symbols set

actual.value: 2020:An open-source mobile AAC app Cboard has entered the final stage of testing for effectiveness with children, professionals and parents. It is expected to be accessible to professionals and children by the end of 2020.

title.narrative: Existence of Augmentative and Alternative Communication (AAC) communication boards on the playgrounds and outdoor spaces for children

actual.value: 2020:This activity has been suspended due to the lack of funds and low interest of the local communities for setting up AAC boards at playgrounds.

title.narrative: Implementation of Neo-BFHI programme at NICUs and neonatal units

actual.value: 2020:Capacity building activities of NICU staff are implemented according to plan (two seminars and one expert meeting are held online). First NICU assessment is delayed for October due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
